egion of choice, he discusses police procedurals set in America, the United Kingdom and Ireland, Europe, Moscow, Asia, and selected locales in other parts of the world, as well as in historical places ranging from the Roman Empire to turn-of-the-century Cairo.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aDetective and mystery stories, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aDetective and mystery stories, EnglishxHistory and criticism. 0aGeography in literature. 0aPlace (Philosophy) in literature. 0aPolice in literature. 0aPopular literaturezEnglish-speaking countriesxHistory and criticism. 0aSetting (Literature). 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Mystery & Detective.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292798328423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292798328/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK